In the recent &ldquo;web 2.0&rdquo; sites, we see cool search boxes, with the search button appearing &ldquo;inside&rdquo; the text box. How&rsquo;d they do that? Microsoft&rsquo;s bing search also has this feature. A snapshot of the bing search box looks like this:

It&rsquo;s actually quite simple to do, with a bit of css. First, let&rsquo;s look at the markup:
[code:html]
&lt;div class=&lsquo;search-box&rsquo;&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;asp:TextBox runat=&ldquo;server&rdquo; ID=&lsquo;txt1&rsquo;&gt;&lt;/asp:TextBox&gt;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;asp:Button runat=&ldquo;server&rdquo; ID=&lsquo;btn1&rsquo; Text=&lsquo;Search&rsquo; /&gt;
